instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "Digital Twin development follows a four‑stage MBSE lifecycle: (1) Requirements – expressed with SysML requirements diagrams; (2) Functional Architecture – defined with component‑and‑connector ADLs (ACME, AADL, MontiArc); (3) Logical Architecture – models component behavior with MontiArc Automata or SysML v1.7 state machines; (4) Product/Technical – translated into executable C++/Java code and validated by simulation in MathWorks Simulink. Each stage uses a distinct modeling notation tailored to its abstraction level."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "Standardization of the twin’s modeling artifacts follows well‑established model‑based engineering specifications. SysML (v1.7) is used for requirements and behavioral modeling, ACME and AADL provide an architecture description language for component interconnection, and MontiArc supplies a formal automaton language for component behavior. For simulation and executable validation, MathWorks Simulink is employed. These technologies align with the industry’s MBSE standards and facilitate interoperability between disparate modeling tools."
]
